  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "Okay, here are some of the best San Francisco coffee shops with reliable Wi-Fi that stay open late enough to accommodate evening work, along with some of their strengths:\n\n**Focusing on Reliability and Work-Friendly Atmosphere:**\n\n*   **Sightglass Coffee (SOMA - 270 7th Street):**\n    *   **Why it's great:** This location often has ample seating, good natural light (early evening), and a dedicated Wi-Fi network.  It is usually quieter compared to some of their more tourist-heavy spots. High-quality coffee.\n    *   **Hours:** Usually open until 6 or 7 PM. Check their website for the exact hours.\n    *   **Vibe:**  Modern, slightly industrial, but generally conducive to focus.\n\n*   **Saint Frank Coffee (Various Locations, but Potrero is good):**\n    *   **Why it's great:** Saint Frank is known for its ethically sourced beans and carefully crafted coffee. The Potrero location is usually open later. It has a good vibe for working without being too loud.\n    *   **Hours:** Check their website. Typically open until 7 PM.\n    *   **Vibe:**  Minimalist, clean, good for quiet focus.\n\n*   **Coffee Bar (Various Locations, but Potrero & Bernal are good):**\n    *   **Why it's great:** Coffee Bar locations tend to have a European-style cafe vibe. The locations listed are usually less crowded than their Financial District one.\n    *   **Hours:** Typically open until 7 PM.\n    *   **Vibe:** Relaxed, less formal than some, but still good for working.\n\n**Later Hours (Typically 8 PM or later):**\n\n*   **Cafe Reveille (Multiple Locations):**\n    *   **Why it's great:** Usually open until 8 PM. Popular spot for a reason, so can get busy!\n    *   **Hours:** Varies, but usually until 8 PM or later.\n    *   **Vibe:** Trendy, can be a bit louder but lively.\n\n*   **Andytown Coffee Roasters (Various Locations):**\n    *   **Why it's great:** A local favorite, Andytown has several locations throughout the city, known for their Snow Petrel coffee drink. Some of the locations stay open until 7-8 PM.\n    *   **Hours:** Varies by location, check their website.\n    *   **Vibe:** Friendly, comfortable, good community vibe.\n\n**Important Considerations When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Wi-Fi Reliability:** Even places advertising Wi-Fi can have issues. Check recent reviews on Yelp or Google Maps to see if there are current complaints about the internet speed or connectivity.\n*   **Seating Availability:**  Weeknights can be surprisingly busy. Consider going early to snag a good spot.\n*   **Noise Level:** Some cafes are naturally louder than others. Look for places with higher ceilings or more space between tables if you need quiet.  Read reviews to get a sense of the sound levels.\n*   **Power Outlets:**  Essential for evening work! Check reviews or call ahead to confirm ample outlet access.\n*   **Your Neighborhood:** Consider which location is most convenient for you to avoid unnecessary travel.\n*   **Food & Drink:** Look for places that offer a decent selection of snacks or light meals if you plan to work for several hours.\n\n**Before You Go:**\n\n*   **Double-Check Hours:**  Always verify the cafe's current hours online (Google Maps, Yelp, or their website) as they can change, especially on holidays or during special events.\n*   **Read Recent Reviews:**  Reviews often mention current Wi-Fi conditions, noise levels, and seating availability.\n*   **Have a Backup Plan:**  If your first choice is too crowded or the Wi-Fi is down, have a second option in mind.\n\nHappy working!\n",
